Setup virtual environment, used for managing dependencies:
    python -m venv venv

Activate virtual environment:
    venv\Scripts\activate.bat

After activating virtual environment:

    Install Django: pip install Django

    Creating Django project: django-admin startproject [project-name]

    Run project: python manage.py runserver

    Creating Django app: python manage.py startapp [app-name]
    Install Django app to project: Add the app-name to the project settings file in INSTALLED-APPS list

    Connect app Urls to project:
        1. Include the urls (look in urls.py of project)
        2. Create urls.py:  echo> [app-folder-name]/urls.py (like 'touch', but touch doesn't work in Windows)